## 2. The meta-diagnosis: the pattern that has to stop

There is a pattern across all three plans (the original tips engine, the Phase 1 Revamp, and now Wave 2), and naming it is the single most useful thing this document can do.

Every plan builds another **engine**. Every plan defers the **data**. The validation gate is — correctly — designed to surface *nothing* until real edge is proven on real history. So each wave ships a new, beautifully-architected component that has nothing to compute edge from, the gate honestly refuses to show anything, and the Tips tab stays blank. The owner opens the app, sees an empty room, and concludes the execution failed.

The execution mostly did not fail. The *plan design* keeps building the part that refuses to lie while perpetually postponing the part that gives it something true to say. Wave 2's own risk section admits this in plain text: ~62 days cached → ~50 rows → "cannot clear n≥50 + DSR≥0.95 + PBO≤0.5… the ML cell stays headline_eligible=False." The plan is telling you, on page one, that it will ship dark.

This document's central claim: **stop adding engines; add data and a useful surface.** Wave 2 as written is the third instance of the pattern. Re-aimed and re-sequenced, it becomes the wave that breaks it.

