## 7. Challenge 5 — Abstention is buried as "optional" when it is the most valuable component

Wave 2 puts `metalabel.py` in as "OPTIONAL/flagged… data-starved scaffolding," while making direction the headline. This is exactly backwards.

Selective abstention (the conformal risk-coverage threshold τ) is the **most data-efficient and most valuable** capability in the whole design. You do not need a great model to abstain well — you only need to know *when* your weak model is confident. And for a buyer, the economics are decisive: "**take 15% of setups at 68%**" beats "take 100% at 54%" by an enormous margin, because the option premium math only works on the high-conviction tail. Trading less is how you buy accuracy; abstention is alpha.

The plan has the priority inverted: direction is first-class, abstention is an afterthought. It should be the reverse. Abstention is the thing you do *most* of the time; direction is the thing you abstain *from*.

**→ The alteration.** Promote selective abstention to a first-class, always-on component — the risk-coverage curve and τ are not optional polish, they are the core deliverable that converts any weak model into a usable high-conviction subset. The headline feed *is* the gated subset.

