## 8. Challenge 6 — The product ships dark because nothing is shown until the gate clears

This is the challenge that most directly addresses your disappointment. The current design surfaces *nothing* until a `(structure, regime)` cell clears the full headline gate. That is why the app reads as empty — and it is an unforced error, because **usefulness does not require proven edge.**

Even today, with zero validated cells, the Tips tab could show, per underlying, something genuinely useful to a buyer:

> *NIFTY 23,500 CE — implied move 1.2%, model-expected realized ~0.9% → option looks ~15% rich; P(touch) 38% in 5 sessions; regime = range-bound; premium-buying unfavorable here.*

That is honest decision context. It requires no `edge_verified`. It is just *surfacing the structural reads you already compute* (VRP, touch probability, regime, IV-crush windows) as analytics, clearly separated from any "edge-proven" claim. The Phase 1 Revamp plan actually called for this — the "Watchlist — developing signals" panel — but it appears to have been built as a placeholder rather than a substantive surface.

The fix is to make that analytics surface **rich** on day one, while keeping the "Edge-proven" headline feed honestly empty until validated. An empty headline must stop meaning an empty product.

**→ The alteration.** Add a first-class analytics/decision-context surface to this wave (or the data wave). It shows the structural reads as honest context — never as gated tips — so the product is substantive *before* any cell clears the gate. This is the single change that most quickly makes Anvil feel like a product.

