## 10. Challenge 8 — The feature set is all state, no dynamics

The feature row is built from `SignalContext` single-day accessors (IV rank, skew, GEX, PCR, max-pain distance, days-to-expiry, crush score) plus a regime one-hot. These are **state** snapshots. There are almost no **dynamics**: no ΔIV-rank, no ΔGEX, no OI velocity, no term-structure-slope changes, no realized-vol trajectory. The plan itself notes the rolling `iv_rank` is the *only* multi-day feature.

Markets transition; predicting a transition usually needs the *rate of change*, not just the level. A model fed only static snapshots is handicapped at exactly the thing you want — anticipating a move — regardless of how good the model is.

(There is a chicken-and-egg here: you cannot *add* features at 50 rows without making the overfitting in Section 4 worse. Which is one more reason the data wave comes first — dynamics features only become safe to add once there is history to fit them on.)

**→ The alteration.** When the ML layer is built (post-data), include path/dynamics features — changes and velocities of the structural reads — not only single-day levels. Until then, do not add features to a 50-row model.

