## 12. The re-sequenced wave map

A concrete reordering that breaks the pattern in Section 2:

**Wave 2 (was W3) — DATA.** Acquire history, pandas-free, with `httpx` + `csv`. This is the wave that lights up everything you already own.

| Data | Source | Unlocks |
|---|---|---|
| Multi-year NSE bhavcopy (NIFTY/BANKNIFTY) | NSE archives | Touch frequencies, VRP history, validation sample size |
| BSE bhavcopy (SENSEX/BANKEX) | BSE archives | SENSEX support |
| Equity cash OHLC (NIFTY-500) | Yahoo chart JSON / NSE | Realized-vol forecasts, future stock ML |
| India VIX history | NSE | Regime gating, VRP context |
| FII/DII + participant-OI history | NSE | Positioning signals |
| Index constituents/weights + sector map | NSE | Cross-sectional → index aggregation |
| Earnings/event calendar | seed CSV → nsepython/jugaad-data | Event-IV-crush target |

**Wave 2.5 — ANALYTICS SURFACE.** Make the Tips tab substantive *now*: surface VRP, touch probability, regime, and IV-crush windows as honest decision context (Section 8), clearly separated from any edge-proven claim. No proven edge required. This is what makes the product stop feeling empty.

**Wave 3 — STRUCTURAL TARGETS + CALIBRATION.** Build targets 1–4 (Section 11) as gated factors, validated through the *existing* harness, scored via the *existing* cost-aware tip resolution. As the data sample is now large, cells can actually clear the gate and `edge_verified` can light up.

**Wave 4 — ML META-LAYER (the reframed engine).** Now build the GBM/meta-labeling, on real history, consuming the structural targets as features, with path/dynamics features included, outputting a calibrated act/abstain decision. This is where the Wave 2 modules belong — alive instead of dormant.

**Wave 5+ — as the existing backlog (news/sentiment, AI research loop, ensemble/regime stacking, transparency UI, intraday).** Unchanged.

