## 13. Smaller flags worth folding in

**The LLM-via-CLI piece is polish, and slightly risky polish.** Shelling out to `claude -p` on the Max subscription for *explanation* (never prediction — and the plan correctly keeps it out of the prediction path) is fine for personal/dev use. But it is a ToS gray area for automated/programmatic use; it must never be load-bearing (the deterministic-narrator default is right); and the moment Anvil serves anyone but you, routing their requests through your personal subscription is both a ToS violation and unscalable. Given your disappointment is about *substance*, spending wave effort on a narration layer misallocates toward polish. De-prioritize it until the substance exists.

**Verify Black-76 is actually live.** The Anvil README describes `greeks.py` as "Black-Scholes-Merton… on spot," but your own ADRs (0002, 0004) and the merged blueprint mandate **Black-76 on the futures price**, because Indian index options settle off futures. If the working base is still BSM-on-spot, that is a correctness bug that quietly poisons every Greek, every IV, and therefore every feature downstream — a five-minute check worth doing before building anything on top.

**On "maximum monetization" — the shape matters more than the ambition.** In India this is not a pure product decision. SEBI's Research Analyst / Investment Adviser regulations govern *recommendations provided for consideration*, and making accuracy or return claims while unregistered is exactly what gets penalized — it is the same conduct behind the enforcement actions the product is positioned against. Selling *predictions/tips for a fee* to other users walks straight into RA/IA registration. But selling the *tooling* — the cross-broker consolidated Greeks book (which genuinely no retail tool offers), the risk cockpit, the calibration dashboard — as software/data, where you hand the user the instrument and do not tell them what to buy, is a far cleaner SaaS posture with very different regulatory exposure. Same code, different legal terrain. **Decide the shape before building toward the money**, because it changes the architecture.

